<div class="content">
	<p>In the upper right corner, you will see line of commonly used apps and controls that relate to the current user who is signed in.   The last item in this list is a clickable item to sign out, ending your current session. </p>

	<div class="figure">
		<img src="images/help/getting-started/using-desktop/session-toolbar.png" />
		<div class="caption">The Session Toolbar</div>
	</div>

	<p>From left to right, the items shown on this toolbar include:</p>
	<ol>
		<li>
			<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-user icon"></i></span>Current User</h3>
			<p>Clicking on this item will launch the <a href="#apps/profile-viewer">Profile Viewer</a> app which is used to show your user profile and other user related information such as your friends and your account details.</p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-newspaper icon"></i></span>News</h3>
			<p>Clicking this icon will launch the <a href="#apps/topic-viewer">News Browser</a> app that you can use to post and view news about your life and the lives of your friends, family and colleagues.</p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-comment icon"></i></span>Chat</h3>
			<p>Clicking this icon will launch the <a href="#apps/chat-browser">Chat Browser</a> app that you can use to exchange private direct messages with your friends.</p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-cog"></i></span>Settings</h3>
			<p>Clicking this icon will launch the <a href="#apps/settings-manager">Settings Manager</a> app where you can view and change your system settings and app preferences.</p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-search icon"></i></span>Connection Finder</h3>
			<p>Clicking this icon will launch the <a href="#apps/connection-manager">Connection Manager</a> app in search mode in order to allow you to search for and connect with new friends.</p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-user-plus icon"></i></span>Connection Requests</h3>
			<p>Mousing over this icon will display a dropdown list of connection requests, which you can accept or decline.  If you have no pending connection requests, then this item will not be shown. </p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle icon"></i></span>Notifications</h3>
			<p>Mousing over this icon will display a dropdown notifications list, which includes notifications of comments, likes, share requests, and other items that require your attention. If you have no pending notifications, then this item will not be shown.</p>
		</li>
	<ol>
</div>